  <problem>

	<p>A small block of mass m slides from the top of a wedge of mass M and height h (see the diagram) until it reaches a horizontal surface. The wedge can also slide along the horizontal surface. The slope of the wedge makes angle &#x3B8; with the horizontal. All surfaces are frictionless and you may assume that the block makes a smooth transition from the wedge to the horizontal surface. The acceleration due to gravity is g. </p>

	<p><img width="699" alt="BK142" src="/static/problems/MIT/rayyan/check_points/Pictures/BK142.png"/></p>

	<p>Part 1. In order to find the speed of the block on the horizontal surface, what physical principles/laws/ideas are best to use?</p>

        <multiplechoiceresponse direction="vertical" randomize="yes" type="MultipleChoice">
          <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
            <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">
				<text>Constant-acceleration kinematics and conservation of energy.</text>
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">
				<text>Constant-acceleration kinematics and conservation of momentum.</text>
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">
				<text>Variable-acceleration kinematics and conservation of energy.</text>
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">
				<text>Variable-acceleration kinematics and conservation of momentum.</text>
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">
				<text>Conservation of energy only.</text>
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">
				<text>Conservation of momentum only.</text>
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil7" correct="true">
				<text>Conservation of energy and conservation of momentum.</text>
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil8" correct="false">
				<text>Newton's laws and conservation of energy.</text>
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil9" correct="false">
				<text>Newton's laws and conservation of momentum.</text>
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil10" correct="false">
				<text>Newton's laws and constant-acceleration kinematics.</text>
            </choice>
          </choicegroup>
        </multiplechoiceresponse>


          <p>Part 2. As the block slides down, the wedge:</p>

        <multiplechoiceresponse direction="vertical" randomize="yes" type="MultipleChoice">
